author: maxb
msg: SWIG bindings documentation improvements (including catchup with the addition
of SWIG 1.3.24 compatibility).
* INSTALL: Clarify the pointer to subversion/bindings/swig, for people who
don't know that the Python/Perl bindings involve SWIG.
* subversion/bindings/swig/README: This is mainly for developers. Rename it...
* subversion/bindings/swig/NOTES: ...to this, to avoid making it sound like a
must-read for end users.
* subversion/bindings/swig/INSTALL (STATUS): Add a status section describing
the completeness of each lanaguage's SWIG bindings.
(BUIDIING ON UNIX): Adapt for 1.3.24. Make a little more language-neutral.
Put a piece of not very relevant text in parentheses. Explain a nice way
to augment the Python library path to include the Subversion bindings
install area.
